3 (2) The Board shall:
4 (i) stream live video or live teleconference audio or other audio of
5 the open meetings of the Board ONLY IF THE MEETING IS HELD AT:
6 1. THE HEADQUARTERS OF THE BOARD; OR
7 2. A LOCATION WHERE THE BOARD HELD AT LEAST 10
8 MEETINGS DURING THE IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING CALENDAR YEAR;
9 (ii) maintain on its website a complete and unedited archived
10 recording of each open meeting that is livestreamed in accordance with this subsection; and
11 (iii) notwithstanding § 3–306(b)(2)(i) of the General Provisions
12 Article:
13 1. prepare minutes of each meeting as soon as practicable
14 after the meeting; and
15 2. publish and maintain on its website the minutes of each
16 open meeting prepared in accordance with this subsection.
17 (3) The inability of the Board to comply with paragraph (2)(i) and (ii) of this
18 subsection due to technical failure that entirely prevents or otherwise affects the quality of
19 the live video or audio streaming of a meeting of the Board does not affect the validity of
20 any action taken by the Board during the meeting if:
21 (i) the Board otherwise complies with this subsection and the Open
22 Meetings Act; and
23 (ii) the inability to comply is not due to willful action by the Board.
24 (4) In addition to complying with the minutes requirements of the Open
